---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import Nav from '../../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Base title="For whom" description="Three learning tracks: Product Designer (N1), System Designer (N2), and Design Engineer (N3). Each with 6 progressive tutorials.">
  <Nav lang="en" />

  <section style="padding: 5rem 0;">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 860px;">
      <p style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.8125rem; color: var(--color-accent); font-weight: 600; margin-bottom: 1rem;">FOR WHOM</p>
      <h1 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 3rem); font-weight: 700; line-height: 1.2; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">
        Three profiles, one system
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size: 1.0625rem; color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.75; margin-bottom: 3.5rem; max-width: 600px;">
        Aplica DS is designed to be useful at different points across the design–engineering spectrum. Each track has 6 progressive tutorials with clear prerequisites and estimated duration.
      </p>

      <!-- N1 -->
      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid #f97316; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <div>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f97316;">TRACK N1</span>
            <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 0.25rem;">Product Designer</h2>
          </div>
          <span style="background: var(--color-accent-bg); color: var(--color-accent-text); font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 99px;">6 tutorials · ~3h</span>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          For designers who use the system in Figma without needing to understand the internal architecture. Track N1 teaches token vocabulary, built-in accessibility, and automatic dark mode.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">What you learn:</p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          {[
            'What tokens are and why they exist',
            'Color vocabulary: brand, interface, product',
            'Dimension scale: minor / normal / major',
            'Tokens in Figma via Tokens Studio',
            'Accessibility by construction (WCAG AA/AAA)',
            'Dark mode without effort',
          ].map(item => (
            <li style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: flex-start;">
              <span style="color: #f97316; flex-shrink: 0;">→</span> {item}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <a href="https://docs.aplica.design/en-US/tutorials/n1-product-designer/N1-01" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size: 0.9rem;">
          Start N1 →
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- N2 -->
      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid #8b5cf6; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 2rem; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <div>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: #8b5cf6;">TRACK N2</span>
            <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 0.25rem;">System Designer</h2>
          </div>
          <span style="background: rgba(139,92,246,0.1); color: #7c3aed; font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 99px;">6 tutorials · ~4h · Prereq: N1</span>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          For those who configure, extend, and govern the system. Track N2 goes deep into the 5-layer architecture, the OKLCh pipeline, and responsible override decisions.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">What you learn:</p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          {[
            '5-layer mental model in depth',
            'OKLCh pipeline: how colors are generated',
            'Config-First paradigm',
            'Anatomy of a complete theme',
            'Product colors: exponential cost and entropy',
            'Responsible overrides: Study → Test → Document',
          ].map(item => (
            <li style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: flex-start;">
              <span style="color: #8b5cf6; flex-shrink: 0;">→</span> {item}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <a href="https://docs.aplica.design/en-US/tutorials/n2-system-designer/N2-01" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size: 0.9rem; background: #8b5cf6;">
          Start N2 →
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- N3 -->
      <div style="border: 1px solid var(--color-border); border-left: 4px solid #10b981; border-radius: var(--radius); padding: 2rem;">
        <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; justify-content: space-between; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
          <div>
            <span style="font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.75rem; font-weight: 700; color: #10b981;">TRACK N3</span>
            <h2 style="font-family: var(--font-display); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; margin-top: 0.25rem;">Design Engineer</h2>
          </div>
          <span style="background: rgba(16,185,129,0.1); color: #059669; font-size: 0.8125rem; font-weight: 600; padding: 0.25rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 99px;">6 tutorials · ~5h · Prereq: N2</span>
        </div>
        <p style="color: var(--color-text-muted); line-height: 1.7; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          For engineers who implement components and integrate tokens in code. Track N3 covers token contract, dark mode by construction, multi-platform integration, and adding new brands.
        </p>
        <p style="font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.875rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">What you learn:</p>
        <ul style="list-style: none; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.4rem; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
          {[
            'Token contract: correct consumption in components',
            'Building a conformant component from scratch',
            'Dark mode by construction (not by override)',
            'Build pipeline in depth',
            'Integration in React, Vue, Next.js, React Native',
            'Adding a new brand to the engine',
          ].map(item => (
            <li style="color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: 0.9375rem; display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; align-items: flex-start;">
              <span style="color: #10b981; flex-shrink: 0;">→</span> {item}
            </li>
          ))}
        </ul>
        <a href="https://docs.aplica.design/en-US/tutorials/n3-design-engineer/N3-01" class="btn btn-primary" style="font-size: 0.9rem; background: #10b981;">
          Start N3 →
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <Footer lang="en" />
</Base>